claim.claim-text:
27. A light emitting device, comprising:
a substrate;
a plurality of light emitting diodes (LEDs) disposed over the substrate in an array;
a retention material disposed at least partially around and proximate to the array of LEDs;
the array of LEDs comprising one or more different patterns of LEDs, wherein at least some of the LEDs in the array are connected in a first pattern that is non-linear and at least some of the plurality of LEDs are electrically connected by wirebonds to form separate strings of LEDs, and wherein each string of LEDs has at least one wirebond that is covered by the retention material.

33. A light emitting device comprising:
a substrate;
a plurality of light emitting diode (LED) chips disposed over the substrate;
at least one electrostatic discharge (ESD) protection device disposed over the substrate; and
a retention material provided over the substrate, wherein the retention material is adapted to retain a filling material over the plurality of LED chips;
wherein the retention material covers the at least one ESD protection device.
